owan University|Rowan Profs]]\n|align=center|[[Mid-Atlantic Collegiate Hockey Association|MACH]]\n|align=center|<ref>{{cite news|last1=Duffy|first1=Nick|title=Rowan DII ice hockey season ends after defeat in regionals|url=http://thewhitonline.com/2017/03/sports/rowan-dii-ice-hockey-season-ends-after-defeat-in-regionals/|accessdate=March 1, 2018|work=The Whit Online|date=March 1, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|2017\u201318\n|align=center|Play-in Round\n|#12 [[TCNJ Lions]]\n|align=center|1\u20136\n|#9 [[Maryland Terrapins]]\n|align=center|[[Mid-Atlantic Collegiate Hockey Association|MACH]]\n|align=center|<ref>{{cite news|last1=Battista|first1=Michael|title=Maryland ends ice hockey\u2019s successful season|url=http://www.tcnjsignal.net/2018/02/26/maryland-ends-ice-hockeys-successful-season/|accessdate=March 1, 2018|work=TCNJ Signal|date=February 26, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" align=\"center\" |2018\u201319\n|align=center|Play-in Round\n| rowspan=\"2\" |#12 [[TCNJ Lions]]\n|align=center|4\u20133\n|#9 [[Rowan University|Rowan Profs]]\n|align=center|[[Mid-Atlantic Collegiate Hockey Association|MACH]]\n|align=center|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://achahockey.org/view/achahockey/divisions/men-s-d2-1/stats-431?type=boxscore&level=game&id=3425825|title=Stats {{!}} ACHA|website=achahockey.org|access-date=2019-03-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://cschc.pointstreaksites.com/view/cschc/news-1470/news_515249|title=TCNJ SHOCKS ROWAN, GIVES COLONIAL 1ST REGIONALS WIN! {{!}} Colonial States College Hockey Conference|last=Battista|first=Michael|date=2019-03-01|website=cschc.pointstreaksites.com|access-date=2019-03-04}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|Round One\n|align=center|1\u20136\n|#3 [[Liberty University|Liberty Flames]]\n|align=center|[[Mid-Atlantic Collegiate Hockey Association|MACH]]\n|align=center|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://achahockey.org/view/achahockey/divisions/men-s-d2-1/stats-431?type=boxscore&level=game&id=3426205|title=Stats {{!}} ACHA|website=achahockey.org|access-date=2019-03-04}}</ref><ref name=TCNJRegional/>\n|-\n|align=center|2019\u201320\n|align=center|Play-in Round\n|#12 [[TCNJ Lions]]\n|align=center|2\u20133 (OT)\n|#9 [[Wake Forest Demon Deacons]]\n|align=center|[[Atlantic Coast Collegiate Hockey League|ACCHL]]\n|align=center|<ref>{{cite web |title=The College of New Jersey vs Wake Forest University 2020 Regionals |url=http://achahockey.org/view/achahockey/divisions/men-s-d2-1/stats-431?type=boxscore&level=game&id=3528659 |website=achahockey.org |accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Battista |first1=Michael |title=REGIONALS RECAP, TCNJ FALLS TO WAKE FOREST |url=http://cschc.pointstreaksites.com/view/cschc/news-1470/news_529908 |website=cschc.pointstreaksites.com |accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Garcia |first1=Anthony |title=Ice hockey loses 3-2 in overtime in first round of regional tournament |url=http://www.tcnjsignal.net/2020/03/02/ice-hockey-loses-3-2-in-overtime-in-first-round-of-regional-tournament/ |website=The Signal |accessdate=8 March 2020 |date=3 March 2020}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[American Collegiate Hockey Association]]\n*[[List of ice hockey leagues]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{Reflist|group=note}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{ACHA Division II}}\n\n[[Category:ACHA Division 2 conferences]]\n[[Category:Ice hockey in New Jersey]]\n[[Category:Ice hockey in Pennsylvania]]\n[[Category:2014 establishments in the United States]]\n", "text_old": "{{distinguish|Colonial Hockey Conference}}\n{{Infobox Athletic Conference\n| name          = Colonial States College Hockey Conference (CSCHC)\n| short_name    = ''The Colonial''\n| established   = 2014\n| logo          = File:Colonial States College Hockey Conference Logo.png\n| logo_size     = 200\n| association   = [[American Collegiate Hockey Association|ACHA]]\n| division      = Division II\n| subdivision   = \n| members       = 11\n| sports        = Men's [[ College ice hockey|ice hockey]]\n| mens          = \n| womens        = \n| region        = [[Southeastern United States|Southeast]]\n| former_names  = \n| commissioner  = John Bullis\n| since         = \n| website       = [http://cschc.pointstreaksites.com/view/cschc Official website]\n| color         = \n| font_color    = \n| map           =\n| map_size      =\n}}\nThe '''Colonial States College Hockey Conference''' ('''CSCHC''') is a [[College ice hockey|college]] [[ice hockey]] league based in the [[Mid-Atlantic (United States)|mid-Atlantic]] region of the United States. The conference is part of the [[American Collegiate Hockey Association]] Division 2 and is made up of ten teams from colleges and universities based in [[New Jersey]] and [[Pennsylvania]].\n\n== History ==\n[[File:Original CSCHC Logo.png|thumb|left|150px|The original logo of the CSCHC. Used from 2014<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://cschc.pointstreaksites.com/view/cschc/news-1470/news_149567|title=WELCOME {{!}} Colonial States College Hockey Conference|website=cschc.pointstreaksites.com|access-date=2019-02-12}}</ref> until 2017.]]\nThe conference was formed on April 14, 2014 by programs previously associated with the [[Great Northeast Collegiate Hockey Conference]] (GNCHC). The original seven members consisted of [[Millersville University of Pennsylvania|Millersville University]], [[New Jersey Institute of Technology]] (NJIT), [[Princeton University]], [[Seton Hall University]], [[The College of New Jersey]] (TCNJ), the [[University of Pennsylvania]] (UPenn), and [[West Chester University]]. The founder and first president of the conference was Tom Hench (2014-2016). Andrew Ducko (2016-) currently resides as the conference president.\n\nPrior to the 2015\u201316 season [[Monmouth University]] joined the conference from the [[Mid-Atlantic Collegiate Hockey Association]] (MACH), raising the total number of teams to eight. In November 2015, the ACHA granted the CSCHC an automatic bid into the ACHA D2 Regional Tournament.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://cschc.pointstreaksites.com/view/cschc/news-1470/news_359055|title=CSCHC RECEIVES AUTO BID {{!}} Colonial States College Hockey Conference|website=cschc.pointstreaksites.com|language=en|access-date=2018-04-29}}</ref> \n\nIn March 2016, [[Rutgers University]] and the [[University of Scranton]] were accepted into the conference from the GNCHC following the 2015\u201316 season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://cschc.pointstreaksites.com/view/cschc/news-1470/news_448161|title=The CSCHC Welcomes Rutgers and Scranton {{!}} Colonial States College Hockey Conference|website=cschc.pointstreaksites.com|language=en|access-date=2018-04-29}}</ref>\n\nFor the 2018\u201319 season the conference adopted a new shootout rule for regular season games that were tied at the conclusion of overtime, eliminating the \"tie\" entirely from CSCHC play. The first game to implement this new rule was on October 26, 2018 where The College of New Jersey defeated Millersville University, 5\u20134 (2:1 in SO), after five shootout rounds.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://acha_cschc.wttstats.pointstreak.com/boxscore.html?gameid=3367582|title=Colonial States College Hockey Conference {{!}} Pointstreak Stats|website=acha_cschc.wttstats.pointstreak.com|access-date=2019-02-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://achahockey.org/view/achahockey/divisions/men-s-d2-1/stats-431?type=boxscore&level=game&id=3367582|title=Stats {{!}} ACHA|website=achahockey.org|access-date=2019-02-13}}</ref>\n[[File:CSCHC 2018 Playoffs.jpg|alt=The College of New Jersey and West Chester University compete in the first round of the 2018 CSCHC Playoffs at Loucks Ice Center.|thumb|The College of New Jersey and West Chester University compete in the first round of the 2018 CSCHC Playoffs at Loucks Ice Center.|278px]]\n\nFollowing that season the CSCHC took part in the 2019 Men's Division 2 All Star Challenge, along with 12 other DII leagues and one group representing independent programs, which was hosted at West Chester's [[Ice Line Quad Rinks]].<ref>{{cite web |title=COLONIAL TO COMPETE IN ACHA D2 ALL-STAR CHALLENGE |url=http://cschc.pointstreaksites.com/view/cschc/news-1470/news_516352 |website=cschc.pointstreaksites.com |accessdate=9 March 2020}}</ref> The team finished 12th with a record of 1-3-1.<ref>{{cite web |title=2019 Men's Division 2 All Star Challenge |url=http://achahockey.org/view/achahockey/events-477/2019-mens-division-2-all-star-challenge |website=achahockey.org |accessdate=9 March 2020}}</ref> In August 2019, TCNJ was announced as a 2020 ACHA Men's Division 2 Regional host, with [[Lawrenceville School#Facilities|Loucks Ice Center]] in [[Lawrenceville, New Jersey]] acting as the site for the Southeast tournament between February 28 and March 1.<ref>{{cite web |title=2020 Men\u2019s Division 2 Regional Sites Selected |url=http://achahockey.org/view/achahockey/acha-hockey-news/news_524892 |website=achahockey.org |accessdate=9 March 2020}}</ref> This was the first time that a team from The Colonial acted as an official host for an official ACHA event. The two teams that advanced to the 2020 National Tournament from this were #3 [[Cincinnati Bearcats|University of Cincinnati]] and #7 [[Miami RedHawks|Miami University]].<ref>{{cite web |title=We would like to thank @achamensd2 for allowing us to host Regionals this year, it was an honor and a great weekend! We would also to say congrats to @MiamiClubHockey & @UCIceHockey for advancing to Nationals, good luck! Also congrats to @TCNJ_Puck on a great season! |url=https://twitter.com/CSCHCicehockey/status/1234308016503164928 |website=Twitter |publisher=@CSCHCicehockey |accessdate=9 March 2020 |language=en |date=1 March 2020}}</ref> The 2020 ACHA National tournament was later canceled due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Gleckler |first1=Jack |title=Hockey: ACHA cancels national tournament over coronavirus concerns |url=https://www.thepostathens.com/article/2020/03/ohio-bobcats-hockey-acha-national-tournament-canceled |website=The Post |accessdate=20 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2020, [[Stockton University]] was announced at the conference's 11th member ahead of the 2020\u201321 season.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Battista |first1=Michael |title=STOCKTON JOINS THE COLONIAL |url=http://cschc.pointstreaksites.com/view/cschc/news-1470/news_530596 |website=cschc.pointstreaksites.com |accessdate=20 April 2020}}</ref> The Ospreys became the first member to jump into Division 2 with its move, most recently playing in the [[Delaware Valley Collegiate Hockey Conference]]'s (DVCHC) National Division at the Division 3 level. The team will also rejoined the ACHA with the move as the DVCHC, at the time of the 2019\u201320 season, was playing under the [[Collegiate Hockey Federation]], a separate non-varsity governing body.\n\n=== Notable Achievements ===\n{| class=\"wikitable mw-collapsible mw-collapsed\"\n!Date\n!Description\n!Player or Team\n!Notes\n|-\n|September 26, 2014\n|First league game\n|[[Millersville University]] & [[Princeton Tigers|Princeton University]]\n|at Lancaster Ice Rink<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://achahockey.org/view/achahockey/divisions/men-s-d2-1/stats-431?type=boxscore&level=game&id=2510966|title=Stats {{!}} ACHA|website=achahockey.org|access-date=2019-07-04}}</ref>\n|-\n|September 26, 2014\n|First league team Win\n|[[Millersville University]]\n|Millersville won, 8\u20131, over Princeton \n|-\n|September 26, 2014\n|First league goal\n|Alex Vukasin of [[Princeton Tigers]]\n|2 minutes and 57 seconds into the 1st period\n|-\n|September 26, 2014\n|First league assist\n|James McNally of [[Millersville University]]\n|Assisted on Millersville\u2019s first goal 4 minutes and 53 seconds into the first period\n|-\n|September 26, 2014\n|First league goalie win\n|Eric Hench of [[Millersville University]]\n|60 minutes played with 12 saves on 13 shots\n|-\n|September 26, 2014\n|First league Power Play Goal\n|Nicholas Mullarkey of [[Millersville University]]\n| scored on Millersville\u2019s seventh goal of the game, 19 