{"title_page": "Dalibor (film)", "text_new": "{{short description|1956 film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Dalibor\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| director       = [[V\u00e1clav Kr\u0161ka]]\n| producer       = \n| writer         = [[Josef Wenzig]] (libretto)<br>[[V\u00e1clav Kr\u0161ka]] (screenplay)\n| starring       = [[V\u00e1clav Bedn\u00e1r]]\n| music          = [[Bed\u0159ich Smetana]]\n| cinematography = Ferdinand Pe\u010denka\n| editing        = \n| distributor    = \n| released       = {{film date|df=yes|1956}}\n| runtime        = \n| country        = Czechoslovakia\n| language       = Czech\n}}\n\n'''''Dalibor''''' is a 1956 Czech  film rendering of the [[Dalibor (opera)|opera of the same name]] by [[Bed\u0159ich Smetana]].<ref>[https://www.csfd.cz/film/5361-dalibor/prehled/ Dalibor] at csfd.cz</ref> Directed by [[V\u00e1clav Kr\u0161ka]], the film was entered into the [[1956 Cannes Film Festival]].<ref name=\"festival-cannes.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.festival-cannes.com/en/archives/ficheFilm/id/3686/year/1956.html |title=Festival de Cannes: Dalibor |accessdate=2 February 2009 |work=festival-cannes.com |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120208092247/http://www.festival-cannes.com/en/archives/ficheFilm/id/3686/year/1956.html |archivedate=8 February 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n* [[V\u00e1clav Bedn\u00e1\u0159]] as [[Vladislaus II of Hungary|King Vladislav]]\n* [[Karel Fiala]] as Dalibor\n* [[V\u011bra Heroldov\u00e1]] as Milada\n* [[P\u0159emysl Ko\u010d\u00ed]] as Budivoj\n* [[Josef Celerin]] as Bene\u0161\n* [[Josef Rousar]] as V\u00edtek\n* [[Jana Ryb\u00e1\u0159ov\u00e1 (actress)|Jana Ryb\u00e1\u0159ov\u00e1]] as Jitka\n* [[Milo \u010cervinka]] as Zdenek\n* [[Lud\u011bk Munzar]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{imdb title|id=0172291|title=Dalibor}}\n* [http://www.csfd.cz/film/5361-dalibor/ DVD info]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Dalibor}}\n[[Category:1956 films]]\n[[Category:1950s musical drama films]]\n[[Category:Czech films]]\n[[Category:Czechoslovak musical drama films]]\n[[Category:Czechoslovak films]]\n[[Category:Czech-language films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by V\u00e1clav Kr\u0161ka]]\n[[Category:Films set in the 1490s]]\n[[Category:Films based on operas]]\n\n\n{{CzechRepublic-film-stub}}\n{{musical-drama-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|1956 film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Dalibor\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| director       = [[V\u00e1clav Kr\u0161ka]]\n| producer       = \n| writer         = [[Josef Wenzig]] (libretto)<br>[[V\u00e1clav Kr\u0161ka]] (screenplay)\n| starring       = [[V\u00e1clav Bedn\u00e1r]]\n| music          = [[Bed\u0159ich Smetana]]\n| cinematography = Ferdinand Pe\u010denka\n| editing        = \n| distributor    = \n| released       = {{film date|df=yes|1956}}\n| runtime        = \n| country        = Czechoslovakia\n| language       = Czech\n}}\n\n'''''Dalibor''''' is a 1956 Czech  film rendering of the [[Dalibor (opera)|opera of the same name]] by [[Bed\u0159ich Smetana]].<ref>[https://www.csfd.cz/film/5361-dalibor/prehled/ Dalibor] at csfd.cz</ref> Directed by [[V\u00e1clav Kr\u0161ka]], the film was entered into the [[1956 Cannes Film Festival]].<ref name=\"festival-cannes.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.festival-cannes.com/en/archives/ficheFilm/id/3686/year/1956.html |title=Festival de Cannes: Dalibor |accessdate=2 February 2009 |work=festival-cannes.com |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120208092247/http://www.festival-cannes.com/en/archives/ficheFilm/id/3686/year/1956.html |archivedate=8 February 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n* [[V\u00e1clav Bedn\u00e1\u0159]] as [[Vladislaus II of Hungary|King Vladislav]]\n* [[Karel Fiala]] as Dalibor\n* [[V\u011bra Heroldov\u00e1]] as Milada\n* [[P\u0159emysl Ko\u010d\u00ed]] as Budivoj\n* [[Josef Celerin]] as Benes\n* [[Josef Rousar]] as V\u00edtek\